sentences: Eric Scott Reed (born June 21, 1970) is an American jazz pianist and composer.
His group Black Note released several albums in the 1990s.
In May 1986, at Colburn School, Reed met Wynton Marsalis, an encounter that would greatly aid his career.
He joined Marsalis's septet a year later, and worked with him from 1990 to 1991 (in 1991–1992 he worked with Joe Henderson and Freddie Hubbard), and again from 1992 to 1995.

In 2010 he joined the Christian McBride combo Inside Straight, which produced the album Kind of Brown.
Three of his albums have charted on the Billboard' Top Jazz Albums chart: 1995's The Swing and I (peak No. 22); 1998's Pure Imagination (peak No. 8); and 1999's Manhattan Melodies (peak No. 21).
